channel.title: I'm working on a 667 server
channel.description:
I'm trying to move home, but it's hard to get the right npc id since the only way i can do it is to try every id with that name, if anyone could tell me how to make it say id on examine that would help a lot!
Thanks, Adam.

item.title: I'm working on a 667 server
item.dc:creator: @Freighted Freighted
item.description:
@Freighted wrote:

You don’t need to get the examine ID unless your using new-found NPCS, that have not been coded to do anything.

Look through NpcSpawn.java or NpcSpawning.java forgot what it was called for 667.

Whatever source it is, should have every npc that is at your current home in there.

Just change the coords ID to what you want. So in-game do ;;pos or ;;coords.
Then switch the coords in the .java file.

EDIT: Other than that, I can help you through skype, or teamviewer. Reply to me back if you wish to do that.

Simple.
